          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λόφος</span></b> : (1)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">crest</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">plume</span> of a helmet, usually of
          horse - hair, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.743</span></i>. (See
          adjoining cuts, and Nos. 3, 11, 12, 16, 17, 35, 73, 116, 122.)—(2)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">back of the neck</span> of animals or of men, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.508</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            10.573</span></i>.—(3) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hill, ridge.</span> (Od.) 
          
